(:summary    "Evaluate calc-expression within ordinary text"
 :created    "2010"
 :updated    "2010"
 :license    "GPL-3"
 :authors    (("U-ITIHQ\\Tobias.Naehring" . "tobias.naehring@rechner64.itihq.local"))
 :maintainer ("U-ITIHQ\\Tobias.Naehring" . "tobias.naehring@rechner64.itihq.local")
 :provided   (calc-inline)
 :keywords   ("tools" "wp")
 :commentary "\
Matlab-like calc.

Main commands:

calc-inline (evaluate one line)

and

calc-inline-region (evaluate active region)

Bind this two function to the keys of your choice.

See doc of calc-inline-mode for comments of the structure of calc sheets.

Changes:
2011-02-08: calc-inline-region also works for the whole buffer (see doc of calc-inline-region).")
